**MOUNTAIN VISTA WATER CO-OP RESPONSIBILITES**

The goal of our Mountain Vista Water Co-Op is to follow the rules and regulations from the Alberta Federation of Rural Water Co-Operatives. The mission of the Water Co-Op is “helping members provide safe, reliable, sustainable and affordable water to rural Albertans”.

**Mountain Vista Water Co-Op  **

Current members April 2023 - April 2024

Keith, Kerri, Dave, Candace, Shane 

**Responsibilities of the Water Co-Op include but ****are ****not limited to****:**

- The Water Co-Op follows the guidelines outlined in the “water user agreement”.

- Fees are paid annually to cover various costs such as power, insurance, repairs and emergency fund. They are agreed to and voted on at the annual AGM. 

- The Water Co-Op is run by community volunteers. 

- Maintenance of water related items such pipes, pumps, and cistern are Water Co-Op business.

- Members are responsible for their own water meter - ie replacement, repairs etc.

- Main method of communication is via email at [mountainvistaad@gmail.com](mailto:mountainvistaad@gmail.com) . There are also secondary methods such as:

- WhatsApp emergency group in case anyone needs to report an emergency … click here [https://chat.whatsapp.com/GO0Af7vDwoq1NMvVNVUIG8](https://chat.whatsapp.com/GO0Af7vDwoq1NMvVNVUIG8) to join.

- Facebook group “Mountain Vista Cabin Owners”

- The roadway and common space are owned by the Water Co-Op. 

- Snow removal - as we need access to the cistern. 

- We are not a Homeowners Association (HOA). 

- Questions or concerns speak with any member of the Water Co-Op or send an email.

**Social committee members **

Current members - Gina, Susie, Kerri, Keith, Dave, & Shane plus whomever would like to participate at any time throughout the year for different events. We have a great group of individuals who work hard making sure the community looks great – this is done not just by the people on this list but many community members.

Social committee responsibilities include but are not limited to:

- Ideas/thoughts towards improving the community. 

- Current communication is via Facebook group “Mountain Vista Cabin Owners” as well as email – any emails that are received and are non water related are forwarded on to social committee. 

- Funds for the community projects or work is generated by donation and pop bottle returns. 

- Included in community concerns are things like garbage removal, lawn maintenance, gas for lawn mower, painting and maintaining common areas (like the fire pit, horseshoe pit, bridge), collecting pop bottles and taking them to the depot, work related to water feature - repairing, maintaining, adding/removing the feature in the spring and winter. 

- Sport field (poles, nets, games) in the cul du sac

- In the common spaces it is helpful if cabin owners can mow/weed whack around common area fences/shrubs, watering and weed pulling in those areas. 

- Be mindful of things you think are improvements might not be improvements for others. 

- If you want to volunteer and are not sure how you can help - reach out via email or Facebook! 

**RCMP ****&**** County **

- Concerns with your neighbours (hopefully this is a last resort issue and you have talked to them directly about any concerns) 

- Speeding on the roadways 

- Concerns with noise

- The dump is open on Wednesday and Saturday and is free to do drop off all types of waste & recycling. 

**Great Canadian Dance (Trevor Kunkle) **

- They own the pond land.  

- You are required to wear life jackets on the pond.

- If you are building a dock, please chat with the Great Canadian Barn Dance for approval 

- We are not allowed to use their playgrounds, washrooms, garbage or any features on the Barn Dance property. We have recently been allowed to walk through during the summer season only.  

**General **

Some items that are community issues (ie garbage removal) have fallen under mountain vista Water Co-Op and that will be discussed at the next AGM. 

We are working on some ideas to still include garbage and grass cutting, which can be discussed and managed at the next AGM - also open to any feedback and thoughts to include at the 2024 AGM. The goal of the social committee is to continue these services for the community. 

Please be kind and respectful to one another.

There are a lot of people in this community that have been here for some time – we are open to feedback if something is not accurate or missing. 

The social committee is always looking for activities and ideas to get the community involved and meeting one another. If you have ideas, please share them or take the initiative and volunteer to organize it.